; the internal split-horizon zone, one template for every site. a real zone file with the
; domain and derived addresses substituted by nix (replaceVars, see _dns-common.nix): this
; resolver's own IP, the edge ingress VIP, a block of one A record per fleet host at its own
; hostIp, and any site-specific extra records. NOTE: replaceVars substitutes every literal
; occurrence of a placeholder token in this file, comments included -- don't write a
; placeholder's own at-sign-delimited name anywhere in prose, or it gets replaced too.
; the wildcard answers every other name under this zone from the edge VIP (fine for HTTP(S)
; vhosts); the per-host and extra records are more-specific and win over it, no special-casing
; needed -- a direct-protocol hostname (SSH, Samba, NFS) needs its own record or it silently
; falls through to the edge VIP, which doesn't speak that protocol. serial is static (1) because
; this zone is generated, never hand-edited or transferred between servers.
$TTL 300
$ORIGIN @domain@.
@   IN SOA ns.@domain@. hostmaster.@domain@. (
        1          ; serial
        3600       ; refresh
        900        ; retry
        604800     ; expire
        300 )      ; negative cache ttl
    IN NS  ns.@domain@.
ns    IN A   @nsIp@
@     IN A   @edgeVip@
*     IN A   @edgeVip@
@extraRecords@
@hostRecords@
